#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn11.18"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.18:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.18:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga "
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 18. Gahaṭṭhavandanāsutta → sakkanamassanasuttaṃ (bj) | sakkanamassanasuttaṃ (1) (s1) | paṭhamasakkanamassanasuttaṃ (s2, s3) | sakka-namassana (1) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn11.18:0.3"
msgid "18. Gahaṭṭhavandanāsutta "
msgstr "18. Who Sakka Worships "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn11.18:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.18:1.2"
msgid "Tatra … pe … etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.18:1.3"
msgid "“bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo mātaliṃ saṅgāhakaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, Sakka, lord of gods, addressed his charioteer Mātali, "

msgctxt "sn11.18:1.4"
msgid "‘yojehi, samma mātali, sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ. Uyyānabhūmiṃ gacchāma subhūmiṃ dassanāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘My dear Mātali, harness the chariot with its team of a thousand thoroughbreds. We will go to a park and see the scenery.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.18:1.5"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkassa devānamindassa paṭissutvā sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ yojetvā sakkassa devānamindassa paṭivedesi: "
msgstr "‘Yes, lord,’ replied Mātali. He harnessed the chariot and informed Sakka, "

msgctxt "sn11.18:1.6"
msgid "‘yutto kho te, mārisa, sahassayutto ājaññaratho. "
msgstr "‘Good sir, the chariot with its team of a thousand thoroughbreds has been harnessed. "

msgctxt "sn11.18:1.7"
msgid "Yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī’ti. "
msgstr "Please go at your convenience.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: añjaliṃ katvā → pañjaliko (bj, pts1) | pañjaliṃ katvā (mr)
msgctxt "sn11.18:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo vejayantapāsādā orohanto añjaliṃ katvā sudaṃ puthuddisā namassati. "
msgstr "Then Sakka descended from the Palace of Victory, raised his joined palms, and revered the different quarters. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.18:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "So Mātali the charioteer addressed Sakka in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.503, sc2
msgctxt "sn11.18:2.1"
msgid "‘Taṃ namassanti tevijjā, "
msgstr "‘Those proficient in the three Vedas worship you, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:2.2"
msgid "sabbe bhummā ca khattiyā; "
msgstr "as do all the aristocrats on earth, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:2.3"
msgid "Cattāro ca mahārājā, "
msgstr "the Four Great Kings, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:2.4"
msgid "tidasā ca yasassino; "
msgstr "and the glorious Thirty. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:2.5"
msgid "Atha ko nāma so yakkho, "
msgstr "So what’s the name of the spirit "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:2.6"
msgid "yaṃ tvaṃ sakka namassasī’ti. "
msgstr "that you worship, Sakka?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn11.18:3.1"
msgid "‘Maṃ namassanti tevijjā, "
msgstr "‘Those proficient in the three Vedas worship me, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:3.2"
msgid "sabbe bhummā ca khattiyā; "
msgstr "as do all the aristocrats on earth, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:3.3"
msgid "Cattāro ca mahārājā, "
msgstr "the Four Great Kings, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:3.4"
msgid "tidasā ca yasassino. "
msgstr "and the glorious Thirty. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn11.18:4.1"
msgid "Ahañca sīlasampanne, "
msgstr "But I revere those accomplished in ethics, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:4.2"
msgid "cirarattasamāhite; "
msgstr "who have long trained in immersion, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:4.3"
msgid "Sammāpabbajite vande, "
msgstr "who have rightly gone forth "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:4.4"
msgid "brahmacariyaparāyane. "
msgstr "to complete the spiritual life. "

# NOTE: This is pretty radical. for the gods to worship ascetics is common, but for them to worship mere ethical householders?
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn11.18:5.1"
msgid "Ye gahaṭṭhā puññakarā, "
msgstr "I also worship those householders, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:5.2"
msgid "sīlavanto upāsakā; "
msgstr "the ethical lay followers "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:5.3"
msgid "Dhammena dāraṃ posenti, "
msgstr "who make merit, Mātali, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:5.4"
msgid "te namassāmi mātalī’ti. "
msgstr "supporting a partner in a principled manner.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn11.18:6.1"
msgid "‘Seṭṭhā hi kira lokasmiṃ, "
msgstr "‘Those who you worship "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:6.2"
msgid "ye tvaṃ sakka namassasi; "
msgstr "seem to be the best in the world, Sakka. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:6.3"
msgid "Ahampi te namassāmi, "
msgstr "I too will worship "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:6.4"
msgid "ye namassasi vāsavā’ti. "
msgstr "those who you worship, Sakka.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.504, sc7
msgctxt "sn11.18:7.1"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna maghavā, "
msgstr "After saying this, Maghavā the chief, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:7.2"
msgid "devarājā sujampati; "
msgstr "king of gods, Sujā’s husband, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:7.3"
msgid "Puthuddisā namassitvā, "
msgstr "having worshipped the quarters "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.18:7.4"
msgid "pamukho rathamāruhī”ti. "
msgstr "climbed into his chariot.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
